vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
title: |md
  # Replication Write Path Sequence
  **Primary-Secondary Async Replication Flow**
| {near: top-center}
shape: sequence_diagram
# Participants
Client
Primary: Primary Node
Secondary1: Secondary 1
Secondary2: Secondary 2
# === WRITE OPERATION ===
Client -> Primary: "SET user:123 = \"alice\""
Primary."① Local Write" {
  Primary -> Primary: Write to local cache
  Primary -> Primary: Update LRU/LFU metadata
  Primary -> Primary: Persist to WAL (optional)
}
# === ASYNC REPLICATION ===
Primary -> Secondary1: "REPLICATE user:123 = \"alice\"" {
  style.stroke: orange
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
Primary -> Secondary2: "REPLICATE user:123 = \"alice\"" {
  style.stroke: orange
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
# === SECONDARY PROCESSING ===
Secondary1."Process Replication" {
  Secondary1 -> Secondary1: Write to local cache
  Secondary1 -> Secondary1: Update LastSync timestamp
}
Secondary2."Process Replication" {
  Secondary2 -> Secondary2: Write to local cache
  Secondary2 -> Secondary2: Update LastSync timestamp
}
# === ACKNOWLEDGMENTS ===
Secondary1 -> Primary: "ACK (success)" {
  style.stroke: green
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
Secondary2 -> Primary: "ACK (success)" {
  style.stroke: green
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
# === CLIENT RESPONSE ===
Primary -> Client: "+OK (write acknowledged)" {
  style.stroke: "#4CAF50"
  style.bold: true
}
# === TIMING ANNOTATION ===
Client."Note: Client ACK sent BEFORE secondary ACKs" {
  style.fill: "#FFF9C4"
  style.stroke: "#FBC02D"
  style.italic: true
}
# === LEGEND ===
legend: |md
  ## Legend
  - **Solid arrows**: Synchronous operations
  - **Dashed orange**: Async replication (fire-and-forget)
  - **Dashed green**: Async acknowledgments
  - **Bold green**: Client response
  ## Consistency Model
  - **Write**: Acknowledged after primary write
  - **Replication**: Asynchronous to secondaries
  - **Read**: May return stale data from secondaries
  - **Replica lag**: Time between primary write and secondary sync
| {near: bottom-right}